}}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== RT-AC56R and RT-AC56R are the same device and both will work with the same firmware image, the name difference is only related to commercial packaging. See [https://forum.openwrt.org/t/upcycling-asus-rt-ac56r/102343 forum thread] for more details.
*Model Num: 90IG0060-BM3G20 :''Wireless-AC1200'', AiCloud support :Linux kernel 2.6.36.4 (brcmarm) {{WiFiCert|WFA19392|04/15/2013}} *[https://www.asus.com/event/network/EOL-product/ ''End-of-Life Product List'' on '''ASUS''']
===Specifications=== *[http://forums.smallnetbuilder.com/showthread.php?t=12578 Overclocking ''RT-AC56U'' on '''SmallNetBuilder'''] {{â€¢}} ''CPU:'' [http://www.broadcom.com/products/Wireless-LAN/802.11-Wireless-LAN-Solutions/BCM4707-4708-4709 BCM4708] @800 MHz :([[Broadcom]] BCM4708A0 per FCC photos), [[Broadcom]] BCM43217/[http://www.broadcom.com/products/Wireless-LAN/802.11-Wireless-LAN-Solutions/BCM4352 BCM4352] :''WLAN:'' 2T2R 802.11n 300Mbps (2.4GHz), 802.11ac 867Mbps (5GHz) :''RAM:'' ''ESMT'' M15F2G16128A-ADB DDR3-1600 (800/667/533MHz) :''USB:'' 1x USB 2.0, 1x USB 3.0
===FCC info=== * The FCC test report specifies the manufacturer of the device as '''Compal''' :(Compal Networking [KunShan]), however, the FCC photos show the board w/ :standard ''[[Arcadyan]]'' (in which [http://www.arcadyan.com/contentpage.aspx?type=infocontent&L2id=1&infoid=3 it appears] ''Compal'' has a [http://www.emsnow.com/newsarchives/archivedetails.cfm?ID=14039 significant stake]) :labels on it (model: [[Arcadyan]] WG6117EAC22-ASU)
*PCB in the FCC photos: :''"RT-AC56U REV 1.60"'' is silkscreened on the (red) PCB :''"RT-AC56U REV 2.00"'' is silkscreened on the (blue) PCB
